Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    public int temperature;
    public boolean isRaining;
    public boolean useUmbrella;

    public WeatherSimulator(int temperature, boolean isRaining) {
        this.temperature = temperature;
        this.isRaining = isRaining;
        this.useUmbrella = false;
    }

    public void decideToUseUmbrella() {
        if (this.isRaining && this.temperature < 25) {
            this.useUmbrella = true;
        }
    }

    public boolean isItCold() {
        return this.temperature < 20;
    }
}",

If an intervention sets isRaining to true at any temperature, will the useUmbrella variable likely be true if temperature is also set below 25?
